The paper deals with high-dimensional machine learning and signal processing, which are typically covered under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the mutual information and free entropy, which are concepts from information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions benchmark models in neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The analysis of the generalized approximate message-passing algorithm suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the perceptron, which is a classic neural network model, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
